                  </hi>. I live at No. 39, Old Broad-street. On the 7th of May, about four o'clock, I was in Houndsditch, carrying a child—I received in<lb></lb>formation, and searched my pocket—I missed a half-crown and a sixpence, which was all I had—I had them safe about ten minutes before—I did not see any one—my attention was on the child in my arms.</p>
